Vector.description: Return a vector from x,y,z pos or from another vector

IsKeyPressed.description: Return true/false if key was pressed

IsKeyDown.description: Return true/false if key is down

CastSpell3.description: Return true/false if key was pressed

SetSkin.description: Set a current skin to a unit with a skinID.

GetTextArea.description: Return the text width and height

DrawCircle.description: Draw a circle around game object

GetTarget.description: Return your target as unit (or nil if none)

GetCursorPos.description: Return cursor position on the screen

GetEnemyHeroes.description: Return all enemy heroes in a table

GetAllyHeroes.description: Return all ally heroes in a table

GetSave.description: used to save data between matches. It can save all data except userdata, even functions !

CreateDirectory.description: Create a directory and return true or false, only works if the folder doesn’t already exist

DirectoryExist.description: Check if a directory exist and return true or false

WriteFile.description: Return true if could write to file; mode is optional

DeleteFile.description: Return true if file is succesfully deleted

GetFileSize.description: Return the size of a file

DelayAction.description: Delays a function call, Delay is in seconds

CursorIsUnder.description: return if cursor is under a rectangle

createSprite.description: Create a sprite object, Files are loaded from “Sprites” folder

WorldToScreen.description: Return screen position based on ingame coordinates

ValidTarget.description: Return true if the target is valid

BuffIsValid.description: Return true if the buff is valid

CountEnemyHeroInRange.description: return number of enemy in range, object is optional

MoveTo.description: The unit move to the X and Z position.

CalcDamage.description: Calculate the damage that can be dealt to the target

CalcMagicDamage.description: Calculate the magic damage that can be dealt to the target

getBuff.description: Return buff object of the specified index

getInventorySlot.description: Return item ID of the specified slot (ITEM_1 to ITEM_6)

NebelwolfisOrbWalkerClass.description: must be called to bind it to a already existing menu/config

SetOrb.description: enable(true) or disable(false) AA and move

TimeToAttack.description: returns true/false depending on if you can reattack again

TimeToMove.description: returns true/false depending on if you can move after AA

CanOrbTarget.description: returns true/false if target is valid and can be attacked

AddPreTickCallback.description: ​Pewalk will execute these function prior to it's own tick (for advanced use only)

BuffCheck.description: ​Returns false if unit has an invulnerability buff, if 'isAttack' is true it will also check for Shen W and Jax Counterstrike​

BreakChannel.description: ​Allows Pewalk to break an active channel1​

CanAttack.description: Returns true if Pewalk can attack, optional delay (seconds) will return if Pewalk can attack in X seconds​

CanMove.description: Returns true if Pewalk can move, optional delay (seconds) will return if Pewalk can move in X seconds​

DisableSkillFarm.description: Disables Pewalks internal skill farming for 'slot', USE THIS WITH CAUTION, THE INTERNAL CALCULATIONS EXTREMELY ACCURATE​

ForceModeToPoint.description: ​Forces Pewalk to orbwalk in 'mode' to 'point', THIS WILL BYPASS KEYS

ForcePoint.description: ​Forces Pewalk to orbwalk to 'point', 'target' can be set to force Pewalk to focus this unit, if 'forceNilTarget' is true Pewalk will not attack any target

GetActiveMode.description: ​Returns a which mode is currently active

GetAggroCount.description: ​​Returns how many ally minions are currently attacking 'minion'

GetBuffs.description: ​​returns a table containing all buffs currently active on 'unit', THIS TABLE WILL ALSO CONTAIN MASTERY DATA

GetCastPos.description: ​Returns predicted position of 'unit', spell must be a table that contains 'speed' and 'delay', THIS IS INTENDED FOR MINION USAGE ONLY​

GetCollision.description: ​​Returns true if there is minion collision between 'from' and 'point' excluding 'unit', 'spell' must be a table that contains 'width', 'delay', and 'length', THIS IS INTENDED FOR MINION USAGE ONLY

GetMinions.description: ​​returns a table containing all enemy and neutral minions

GetSkillFarmTarget.description: returns a minion that can be killed with a spell, will only return if the minion cannot be killed with an AA: ​'delay' is in seconds: ​'damage' is a function that returns the damage of the skill: 'addSavagery' is true if the Savagery mastery applies to the skill (Most single target spells): 'isSkillshot', true if the spell is a skillshot

GetTarget.description: ​returns a hero target if possible: 'addBoundingRadius' will add the targets boundingRadius to the range, this should be true for most target spells: ​'from' can be nil or a position: 'isAA' is true if the target is for auto attacks

IsHighPriority.description: ​returns true if 'unit' is a high priority target, optional priorityValue can be set to adjust the minium priority (default is 2, 1 = highest priority, 5 = lowest priority)​

SetRangeColor.description: ​​Sets the color of the AA range circle

ValidTarget.description: returns true if the target is valid: ​'range', optional: 'addBoundingRadius', optional, true for most targeted spells: ​'from', optional, myHero is default: 'isAA', optional, true if checking validity for auto attacks

WaitForMinion.description: returns true if Pewalk is waiting to kill a minion in Lane Clear or Mixed Mode​

SetUpdateRange.description: Set the update ranges for different SacUnit types. Explained above in SacUnit section.

Hook.description: Hooks allow you to inject your own code into some of SAC's decision making processes and alter the result.

DisableMovement.description: Disables movement but allows SAC to continue to farm correctly by holding position to cancel attack aggro when necessary.

HardDisableMovement.description: Disables movement and SAC won't manage your attack aggro. Lane clearing will suck as the game will blindly continue to attack.

EnableMovement.description: Cancels both of the above functions, re-enabling all movement.

OrbwalkMode.description: Disables skill farm, jungle skills and champion skills

DisableSkillFarm.description: Disables all skill farming, including under towers

DisableJungleSkills.description: Disables all skill use on jungle monsters

EnableJungleSkills.description: Re-enables all skill use on jungle monsters

DisablePlayerSkills.description: Disables casting any skills on champions

ForceMode.description: Force the given mode. Call again with nil to disable.

ChannelDetectionEnabled.description: Enabled by default. If disabled, SAC will no longer pause while channeling.

PreferredOrbwalkPoint.description: SAC will orbwalk to this point, but only when it was going to move anyway. Options like: <mouse over hero to stop move> can still be used by the user.

ForceOrbwalkPoint.description: SAC will orbwalk to this point. It will ignore user preferences and will not block off-screen movement commands.

SetTSRange.description: Set the range that SAC can search for enemies outside of orbwalk range. By default this is the highest range of SAC's supported skills for this champion.

SetPreferredTarget.description: When SAC is specifically looking for a champion target, it will prioritise this target if it is in range for the actions the script wants to perform. This is the ideal function to use, as it will allow the user to still perform any action they want such as farming, target lock etc, but your target will be prioritized over any other champion when SAC is choosing a champion target.

ForcePreferredTarget.description: SAC will always target this champion when it's within the range you set. This will override all other target selection and in doing so will disable farming, focus selected target, target lock and more. When the target is not within range, normal functionality resumes.

ForceTarget.description: This is absolute. SAC will not target anything other than this champion no matter where they are, whether they're dead, not visible etc.

UnlockTarget.description: Cancels any of the above target modifications.

GetTarget.description: Returns a SacUnit and a reason. The reason is why this unit is targeted, and can be any of the following

AnyModeActive.description: Returns whether any mode is currently active in SAC.

GetActiveMode.description: Returns a string for the current active mode. nil if no mode active.

CanMove.description: Returns false when you are attacking. Same as myHero.moveReady

CanAttack.description: Returns whether your champion can physically attack now, but does not necessarily mean that SAC will attack.

AllowedToMove.description: Returns whether SAC is allowed to perform a movement now, including all option checks, humanizer checks etc.

AllowedToAttack.description: Returns whether SAC is allowed to perform an attack now, including all option checks, humanizer checks etc.

SetOrbwalkPriority.description: By default, SAC will always prioritise champions in orbwalk range. Set this to false to give priority to champions outside of orbwalk range.

CanOrbwalkTarget.description: Returns whether this unit can be attacked. Same as target.iCanOrbwalk for SacUnits.

CanOrbwalkTargetAdditionalRange.description: Returns whether this target could be attacked if you gained x range.

GetLevelAdvantage.description: Returns the level advantage for your team. Negative if you're behind.

GetLevelAdvantageDamagePercent.description: Returns the overall percent damage increase for this minion based on team level advantage and tower advantage in its lane. Negative if behind.

GetLevelAdvantageDefenseAmount.description: Returns the defense increase for this minion based on team level advantage and tower advantage in its lane. 0 if behind.

IsKillable.description: Returns whether the minion is killable with an auto attack and meets all requirements to be attacked (range etc).

IsAlmostKillable.description: Returns whether the minion will very soon be killable with an auto attack, and is not very far from orbwalk range.

IsValidLaneClearTarget.description: Returns whether it's safe to attack this minion without worrying about losing the last hit. Considers auto attack damage only.

CanExecuteMinion.description: Returns whether this minion can be executed with Spoils of War (Relic shield items). Requires you to have a stack of Spoils of War.

LoadPrediction.description: Loads the chosen prediction if it's not already loaded. Predictions will always be loaded before they are used, but it's better to ensure the prediction is already loaded rather than load it when trying to cast a skill for the first time.

GetPrediction.description: Returns castPosition, hitChance from the selected prediction.

UniqueChampionsKilled.description: Returns the number of unique champions you have killed. Persistant during reloads, but SAC had to be loaded when the kill happened.

GetSpoilStacks.description: Returns the number of Spoils of War stacks you have, if any.

GetGamePhase.description: 1 = Early, 2 = Mid, 3 = Late. This is a user-controlled variable. Some users won't use this feature, and game phase will always be 1.

GetTowerCount.description: Returns a table. Values indicate how many towers are remaining in a given position. Example: GetTowerCount().Ally.Top

ValidTarget.description: Similar to normal ValidTarget except contains some humanizer checks from user settings such as minimum time visible.

ValidUnit.description: Like ValidTarget except without checking specific targeting requirements

EnemiesInRange.description: Returns the number of enemies in range. nil range will return number of attackable enemies.

AlliesInRange.description: Returns the number of allies in range. Range cannot be nil.

LeftMouseDown.description: Returns whether left mouse is down

PosOnScreen.description: Returns true if the given position is on-screen. pos can be anything with x, y, z value. You can also use unit.isOnScreen with SacUnits.

KeyToString.description: Converts _Q to Q, _W to W etc.

RandomFloat.description: Returns a random float between min and max.

GetKeyString.description: Will attempt to return the correct name for a given key. For example GetKeyString(32) will return Space.

SaveForThisGame.description: Will save data any data for this game.

LoadForThisGame.description: If data has been saved for this game with this name, it will be returned. nil if no data or new game. Useful for preserving data between BoL reloads.

SaveForThisChamp.description: Will save data specifically for this champion. You can use the same name on another champion to save separately for them.

LoadForThisChamp.description: If data has been saved for this champion with this name, it will be returned. nil if not found.

LoadData.description: Loads data for the given name. nil if not found.

VPrediction.description: Initialize a table of type VPrediction

normalized.description: return a new Vector normalize from vector

rotate.description: Rotate the vector by phi angle

rotated.description: Return a new Vector rotate from vector by phi angle

projectOn.description: Return a new Vector from vector projected on v

mirrorOn.description: Return a new Vector from vector mirrored on v

center.description: Return center between vector and v

angleBetween.description: Return the angle formed from vector to v1,v2

GetPredictedHealth.description: Get the unit predicted health: Health

GetCircularCastPosition.description: Get a circular spell cast position: CastPostion, Hitchance

GetLineCastPosition.description: Get a line skill shot cast position: CastPosition, Hitchance

GetPredictedPos.description: Get the predicted position of the unit: CastPosition, Hitchance

GetCircularAOECastPosition.description: Get a circular aoe skill shot cast position: mainCastPosition, mainHitChance, points, mainPosition

GetLineAOECastPosition.description: Get a line aoe skill shot cast position: mainCastPosition, mainHitChance, MaxHit, Positions

GetConeAOECastPosition.description: Get a cone aoe skill shot cast position: mainCastPosition, mainHitChance, maxHit
